{
  "texts": [
    "The first are hard stop-words whose presence anywhere in the entity string indicated a false positive and thus led to deletion of the sentence from the database.",
    "Examples of those words are \"alloy,\" \"fibers,\" or \"nanotube.\"",
    "If a sample contained the entity \"Al-Mg alloy,\" the phase entity was removed entirely from the database along with its associated sentence, property, and relationship.",
    "The second type are soft stop-words that were simply removed from the entity while the rest was preserved.",
    "Examples of soft stop words include \"precipitate,\" \"intermetallic,\" or \"particle:\" the entity \"Mg2Si precipitate\" would change to \"Mg2Si\"."
  ]
}